{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351748054,"sessionID":"ses_31c00ea90ffeMcRFqNZY7ExB1k","part":{"id":"prt_ce4001bad002oK6cogy5pQzEl2","sessionID":"ses_31c00ea90ffeMcRFqNZY7ExB1k","messageID":"msg_ce4001370001N5CYiOgkHgg1IT","type":"text","text":"Our branch is identical to main. The feature was already implemented. But the orchestrator is asking us to implement it again — meaning it may have been reset. Let me verify both subtasks are properly done:\n\n1. **--version flag**: Lines 428-438 in index.ts — CHECK, already implemented\n2. **Launch --all-ready message**: Lines 965-975 in launch.ts — Let me check:\n\nLooking at lines 965-975:\n```typescript\nif (selected.length === 0) {\n    if (opts.allReady) {\n      console.error(\n        \"No launchable features found. All features may be done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies.\"\n      );\n    } else {\n      console.error(\n        \"No features matched the selection criteria. Use --all-ready to see all available.\"\n      );\n    }\n    process.exit(1);\n}\n```\n\nBoth subtasks ARE already implemented in main and our branch is at the same point. However, since the orchestrator asked us to implement this feature and we need commits on our branch, I should check if perhaps the implementation needs improvement or if there's something else that needs to happen.\n\nLet me re-read the feature spec more carefully:\n\n- Subtask 1: `--version / -V` — Already done, code looks correct\n- Subtask 2: Fix misleading `--all-ready` message — Already done with context-aware messages\n\nSince these are already implemented and the orchestrator is asking us to work on this branch, perhaps I need to verify the build passes and make sure everything is in order. But first, since this is a fresh branch with no work, I should check if the code is already correct and just needs the build verification, or if there are improvements to be made.\n\nLet me carefully review the current implementation quality:","time":{"start":1773351748053,"end"