{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351812858,"sessionID":"ses_31c00ea90ffeMcRFqNZY7ExB1k","part":{"id":"prt_ce40120d9002VoVP1INNGPBFZS","sessionID":"ses_31c00ea90ffeMcRFqNZY7ExB1k","messageID":"msg_ce4011948001SyBZ1WETLAzZJP","type":"text","text":"Let me look at the version handling more carefully and improve it. Currently:\n\n1. The `--version` flag in `parseArgs` (line 233) is used for the `upgrade` command, conflicting with the standard `--version` flag meaning. This is fragile.\n2. The version output could handle edge cases better.\n\nLet me refine the implementation. I'll rename the upgrade's `--version` flag in parseArgs to avoid the semantic confusion, and ensure the version flag is handled cleanly:\n\nActually wait, the upgrade `--version` flag is important for its current purpose (`wombo upgrade --version v1.0.0`). The conflict is only semantic, not functional, because `wombo --version` is caught at the command level before the flag-level parsing. The current code is fine.\n\nLet me instead focus on what's actually needed. Since both subtasks are already implemented, I should look at whether there are any edge cases or issues. Let me re-examine both implementations:\n\nFor subtask 1, the implementation uses `readFileSync` which is fine but could use Bun's `Bun.file()` API per project conventions. Let me make that improvement:","time":{"start":1773351812858,"end":1773351812858}}}
